l´m used to people not helping me.

01:44:57.589 --> 01:45:00.718
Oh, Christ.
Not that self-pity father bullshit.

01:45:02.595 --> 01:45:04.430
What did you say?

01:45:09.602 --> 01:45:11.686
Man, fuck you, William!

01:45:12.103 --> 01:45:15.108
The real bullshit
is you letting me take it on this one...

01:45:15.108 --> 01:45:19.570
...´cause you´re scared to walk out the door
and do something for someone else.

01:45:22.114 --> 01:45:24.408
That´s the only damn reason.

01:45:25.618 --> 01:45:28.119
You don´t know a damn thing
about reasons.

01:45:28.119 --> 01:45:30.123
There are no reasons!

01:45:30.123 --> 01:45:33.333
Reasons why some of us live
and some of us don´t.

01:45:33.625 --> 01:45:36.629
Fortunately for you,
you´ve decades to figure that out.

01:45:36.629 --> 01:45:41.049
What´s the reason for having a locked
cabinet of writing no one can ever read?

01:45:43.135 --> 01:45:45.012
What is that, man?

01:45:47.640 --> 01:45:49.767
l´m done with this shit.

01:45:58.650 --> 01:46:01.362
Look, Jamal is here to pay us a visit.

01:46:06.159 --> 01:46:07.701
What´s up?

01:46:09.161 --> 01:46:10.663
What´s up, y´all?

01:46:10.663 --> 01:46:12.123
Come on.

01:46:40.191 --> 01:46:43.195
How does your first game
in the Garden feel?

01:46:44.696 --> 01:46:47.115
A little closer than I thought.

01:46:47.700 --> 01:46:51.370
That´s why I thought
it might be a good time for us to talk.

01:46:51.703 --> 01:46:56.375
I know it´s been hard handling classes with
the time you have to spend on the court.

01:46:56.709 --> 01:46:59.544
I couldn´t handle it, not at this school.

01:47:00.212 --> 01:47:03.298
Maybe it was unfair of us
to ask you to do it.

01:47:04.216 --> 01:47:07.386
I talked to the board members
and to Crawford...

01:47:08.220 --> 01:47:09.721
...and...

01:47:10.222 --> 01:47:13.600
...we don´t want to pursue this
any more than you do.

01:47:13.725 --> 01:47:17.771
So, l´m here to present you with an offer.
We forget the whole thing.

01:47:18.731 --> 01:47:22.234
Next year, your academic schedule
will be less demanding.

01:47:22.234 --> 01:47:23.736
Crawford wanted that?

01:47:23.736 --> 01:47:26.405
Crawford wants what´s best for you...

01:47:27.239 --> 01:47:28.740
...and for the school.

01:47:28.740 --> 01:47:30.742
What am I supposed to do?

01:47:30.742 --> 01:47:34.247
You hold up a championship trophy
at the end of this tournament.

01:47:34.247 --> 01:47:37.416
You make that happen,
l´ll make the rest happen.

01:47:38.751 --> 01:47:40.252
All right?

01:47:40.252 --> 01:47:42.963
Now, go finish up what you came to do.

01:47:49.761 --> 01:47:51.681
Let´s go, Pilgrims!

01:47:53.265 --> 01:47:55.434
Let´s go! Throw to Jamal!

01:48:24.296 --> 01:48:26.214
Damn, man. Come on.

01:48:27.299 --> 01:48:28.759
Defence!

01:48:41.814 --> 01:48:43.773
Jamal, get the ball!

01:49:01.833 --> 01:49:03.585
Good pass, man.

01:49:11.843 --> 01:49:13.428
Pick it up.

01:49:24.356 --> 01:49:26.525
Offensive foul! That way!

01:49:26.859 --> 01:49:29.235
10, Gold. Offensive! That way.

01:49:30.362 --> 01:49:32.614
You got them now. Let´s go.

01:49:45.376 --> 01:49:46.878
Time-out.

01:49:48.380 --> 01:49:52.592
This is still our game. We stop here,
they´lI have to put us on the line.

01:49:53.384 --> 01:49:57.055
When that happens, it´s all over.
Don´t lose your composure.

01:49:57.889 --> 01:50:02.310
If they score, we don´t call a time-out.
The ball goes to Hartwell or Wallace.

01:50:03.394 --> 01:50:06.022
Okay? Hartwell or Wallace. Let´s go.

01:50:07.898 --> 01:50:09.150
Go!

01:50:23.414 --> 01:50:25.249
What´s the score?

01:50:25.416 --> 01:50:27.628
lt ain´t looking good, Ma.

01:50:39.431 --> 01:50:41.640
Foul. 22, Blue. Two shots.

01:50:45.437 --> 01:50:48.606
Foul, Blue team, 22.
Hit, two. Go line up, guys.

01:50:57.449 --> 01:50:58.992
Two shots.

01:51:02.454 --> 01:51:04.455
We´re going to make these.

01:51:04.455 --> 01:51:07.459
-I can´t look.
-lt´s gonna be all right, Ma.

01:51:17.969 --> 01:51:19.345
Do it.

01:51:27.478 --> 01:51:28.814
Damn.

01:51:34.986 --> 01:51:36.487
One shot.

01:52:04.015 --> 01:52:05.641
That´s game.

01:54:56.563 --> 01:54:59.648
Thank God.
He must have come in after we left.

01:55:00.566 --> 01:55:02.068
Let him sleep.

01:55:02.068 --> 01:55:05.362
-l´ll turn the light off.
-Turn it off and come on.

01:55:12.078 --> 01:55:14.913
You started cleaning up your room, Jamal.

01:55:30.096 --> 01:55:33.182
He looks very happy with himself,
that coyote.

01:55:51.617 --> 01:55:53.952
Jamal, he wrote that for you.

01:55:55.621 --> 01:55:56.956
When?

01:55:57.123 --> 01:55:58.874
After the game.

01:55:59.124 --> 01:56:02.044
He´s going back to the school this morning.

01:56:03.129 --> 01:56:04.629
lt´s funny, though.

01:56:04.629 --> 01:56:07.299
They always let you get but so far...

01:56:07.633 --> 01:56:10.511
...before taking everything away from you.

01:56:11.136 --> 01:56:15.265
God, he´s such a good kid, man.
Then he gets to come back to this shit.

01:56:57.183 --> 01:56:59.060
ls that seat open?

01:57:01.186 --> 01:57:02.771
I think so.

01:57:04.189 --> 01:57:06.983
This isn´t where I thought l´d find you.

01:57:09.194 --> 01:57:11.195
lt´s still my school.

01:57:12.196 --> 01:57:15.493
They want me out,
they´lI have to do it themselves.

01:57:15.701 --> 01:57:17.244
They will.

01:57:18.203 --> 01:57:19.705
Whatever.

01:57:32.718 --> 01:57:37.139
´´The winter´s darkness and cold is but
a momentary prelude to the new spring.

01:57:37.723 --> 01:57:41.768
´´And while its grip seems endless
our own perseverance proves equal.

01:57:42.727 --> 01:57:44.230
´´We renew ourselves once again...

01:57:44.230 --> 01:57:47.649
´´...seeking out the bright moments
that will serve...

01:57:48.233 --> 01:57:50.777
´´...that will serve therefore....

01:57:52.737 --> 01:57:56.073
´´Therefore serve
as the foundation of our future.´"

01:57:57.742 --> 01:57:59.285
Thank you.

01:58:09.254 --> 01:58:11.173
Professor Crawford.

01:58:14.258 --> 01:58:16.345
May I read a few words?

01:58:21.767 --> 01:58:23.810
What is he doing here?

01:58:25.270 --> 01:58:27.606
Yes, of course, by all means.

01:58:30.776 --> 01:58:32.778
Thank you, Professor.

01:58:46.792 --> 01:58:49.128
My name is William Forrester.

01:58:55.801 --> 01:58:57.343
Excuse me.

01:59:02.807 --> 01:59:04.476
l´m that one.

01:59:08.813 --> 01:59:10.523
Losing Family.

01:59:12.317 --> 01:59:15.403
´´Losing family obliges us
to find our family.

01:59:18.324 --> 01:59:21.284
´´Not always the family that is our blood...

01:59:21.326 --> 01:59:24.413
´´...but the family
that can become our blood.

01:59:25.329 --> 01:59:29.250
´´Should we have the wisdom
to open our door to this new family...

01:59:30.335 --> 01:59:34.757
´´...we will find that the wishes we had
for the father, who once guided us...

01:59:36.341 --> 01:59:39.386
´´...for the brother, who once inspired us....

02:00:15.880 --> 02:00:18.549
´´The only thing left to say will be:

02:00:18.883 --> 02:00:22.971
´´´I wish I had seen this,
or I wish I had done that, or I wish....´´"

02:00:26.390 --> 02:00:28.685
Most of you are too young...

02:00:29.894 --> 02:00:32.521
...to know what your wishes will be.

02:00:32.897 --> 02:00:35.274
But when I read these words...

02:00:36.402 --> 02:00:38.653
...words of hope, dreams...

02:00:40.905 --> 02:00:43.199
...I realise that the one...

02:00:43.407 --> 02:00:46.661
...wish that was granted to me,
so late in life...

02:00:47.912 --> 02:00:50.289
...was the gift of friendship.

02:00:53.919 --> 02:00:58.632
Mr. Forrester, l´m sure I speak on behalf
of everyone in thanking you for this visit.

02:01:00.925 --> 02:01:02.426
The quality...

02:01:02.426 --> 02:01:04.345
...of your words...

02:01:04.929 --> 02:01:08.016
...is something we should
all aspire to reach.

02:01:14.439 --> 02:01:17.233
May I ask to what do we owe this honour?

02:01:18.943 --> 02:01:20.945
Professor Crawford...

02:01:21.946 --> 02:01:25.825
...I spoke here today
because a friend of mine wasn´t allowed to.

02:01:27.452 --> 02:01:30.580
A friend who had
the integrity to protect me...

02:01:31.456 --> 02:01:34.208
...when I was unwilling to protect him.

02:01:35.960 --> 02:01:38.170
His name is Jamal Wallace.

02:01:43.969 --> 02:01:46.470
Jamal Wallace is a friend of yours?

02:01:46.470 --> 02:01:48.055
Yes, he is.

02:01:50.474 --> 02:01:54.229
I helped him find his own words
by starting with some of mine.

02:01:55.480 --> 02:01:57.649
In return, he promised...

02:01:58.983 --> 02:02:01.527
...never to say anything about me.

02:02:03.988 --> 02:02:06.115
A promise which he kept.

02:02:08.492 --> 02:02:12.371
While your visit seems heartfelt,
l´m sure you will appreciate...

02:02:12.997 --> 02:02:15.667
...it will not change or interfere...

02:02:16.501 --> 02:02:20.755
...with this institution reaching a fair
and proper decision in this case.

02:02:21.005 --> 02:02:23.299
There´s one more issue here.

02:02:25.510 --> 02:02:27.971
Those words that I read today...

02:02:30.014 --> 02:02:32.016
...I didn´t write them.

02:02:32.016 --> 02:02:33.893
Jamal Wallace did.

02:02:44.028 --> 02:02:45.405
Quiet.

02:02:48.532 --> 02:02:50.243
Quiet, please.

02:02:51.035 --> 02:02:52.536
Be still.

02:02:55.039 --> 02:02:56.750
Quiet, please.

02:02:57.541 --> 02:02:59.585
That has no bearing...

02:03:00.044 --> 02:03:02.547
...on the decision concerning Mr.--

02:03:02.547 --> 02:03:06.050
As director of this competition,
I have final say in this matter.

02:03:06.050 --> 02:03:07.885
Robert, sit down.

02:03:08.052 --> 02:03:11.096
I have been a teacher
for more than 30 years.

02:03:11.555 --> 02:03:15.351
That´s long enough to know
that integrity counts for something.

02:03:15.559 --> 02:03:18.521
l´d say that Mr. Forrester has cleared up...

02:03:19.063 --> 02:03:20.564
...this matter...

02:03:20.564 --> 02:03:24.652
...very nicely for us all.
As chairman of the Faculty Board, I have...

02:03:25.068 --> 02:03:27.529
...the last word in that matter.

02:03:28.072 --> 02:03:31.075
You are excused
from next week´s board meeting.

02:03:31.075 --> 02:03:32.868
Mr. Forrester...

02:03:34.078 --> 02:03:37.706
...should you ever be interested
in a teaching position....

02:03:38.082 --> 02:03:39.333
No.

02:03:41.585 --> 02:03:43.880
Jamal, these are your words?

02:03:47.092 --> 02:03:48.551
Sixteen.

02:03:50.094 --> 02:03:51.679
Remarkable.

02:04:19.123 --> 02:04:22.668
l´m thinking you´ll make
your own decisions from here on.

02:04:24.128 --> 02:04:27.589
I thought you´d say something like,
´´l always could.´´

02:04:28.131 --> 02:04:31.094
No more lessons.
I have a question, though.

02:04:32.636 --> 02:04:35.723
Those two foul shots
at the end of the game...

02:04:36.641 --> 02:04:39.518
...did you miss them or did you miss them?

02:04:41.145 --> 02:04:43.730
Not exactly a soup question, is it?

02:04:45.649 --> 02:04:47.151
Let´s go.

02:04:49.653 --> 02:04:53.783
Do you think our vaudeville act today
will merit the National Enquirer?

02:04:54.158 --> 02:04:55.742
Definitely.

02:04:57.661 --> 02:04:59.871
Whatever happens, l´m off.

02:05:02.166 --> 02:05:05.669
What´s the word
you and your friends would use for that?

02:05:06.169 --> 02:05:07.629
Leaving?

02:05:08.172 --> 02:05:09.632
Oh, God.

02:05:10.174 --> 02:05:11.675
Where are you off to?

02:05:11.675 --> 02:05:14.761
I have a homeland
I haven´t seen for too long.

02:05:15.179 --> 02:05:17.013
You mean lreland.

02:05:17.181 --> 02:05:19.183
Scotland, for God´s sake.

02:05:19.183 --> 02:05:21.394
l´m messin´ with you, man.

02:05:23.186 --> 02:05:25.022
Be sure to write.

02:06:01.724 --> 02:06:03.226
What´s up, John?

02:06:03.226 --> 02:06:05.229
You heard from William?

02:06:05.229 --> 02:06:09.900
Yeah, but I don´t know what he´s doing.
He just checks up on the college recruiters.

02:06:11.235 --> 02:06:14.237
I was just downstairs.
Looks like you got another one.

02:06:14.237 --> 02:06:15.572
Word?

02:06:16.239 --> 02:06:17.990
See you around.

02:06:24.748 --> 02:06:27.459
-Steve Sanderson.
-How are you doing?

02:06:27.751 --> 02:06:29.752
Thanks for coming down on short notice.

02:06:29.752 --> 02:06:31.338
No problem.

02:06:31.755 --> 02:06:33.256
What school are you from?

02:06:33.256 --> 02:06:36.385
No. l´m a lawyer.
I work with Roberts & Carter.

02:06:38.262 --> 02:06:39.263
-A lawyer.
-Yeah.

02:06:39.263 --> 02:06:42.224
But congratulations on all that. lt´s great.

02:06:44.268 --> 02:06:47.437
A bunch of guys in the office
are following you.

02:06:49.272 --> 02:06:52.651
We´re the legal representation
for William Forrester.

02:06:54.278 --> 02:06:55.821
How is he?

02:06:56.781 --> 02:06:58.281
Sit down.

02:07:04.787 --> 02:07:07.834
We´ve received word
that William passed away.

02:07:19.303 --> 02:07:20.845
l´m sorry.

02:07:27.310 --> 02:07:29.438
He wanted you to have...

02:07:29.813 --> 02:07:32.065
...these things right away.

02:07:47.330 --> 02:07:49.040
What happened?

02:07:50.333 --> 02:07:52.252
William had cancer.

02:07:54.338 --> 02:07:56.965
They found it a couple of years ago.

02:08:07.851 --> 02:08:09.853
Jamal, this is crazy.

02:08:10.353 --> 02:08:11.938
Oh, my God.

02:08:16.359 --> 02:08:18.486
Look at all these books.

02:08:18.862 --> 02:08:20.863
Don´t touch anything.

02:09:39.441 --> 02:09:40.943
Dear Jamal..

02:09:40.943 --> 02:09:44.448
Someone I once knew wrote
that we walk away from our dreams...

02:09:44.448 --> 02:09:48.285
...afraid that we may fail, or worse yet,
afraid we may succeed.

02:09:49.953 --> 02:09:53.915
While I knew so very early on
that you would realise your dreams...

02:09:54.457 --> 02:09:57.877
...I never imagined
I would once again realise my own.

02:09:59.463 --> 02:10:00.964
Seasons change, young man.

02:10:00.964 --> 02:10:05.552
While I waited until the winter of my life
to see what I´ve seen this past year...

02:10:06.969 --> 02:10:11.265
...there is no doubt I would have
waited too long, had it not been for you.

02:10:21.484 --> 02:10:23.861
You gonna be here awhile, man?

02:10:27.490 --> 02:10:29.491
Just can´t watch the eyes this time.

02:10:29.491 --> 02:10:31.828
You´ll be okay, man. Come on.

02:10:34.997 --> 02:10:36.666
Come on, man.

02:10:37.500 --> 02:10:38.918
Get up.

